240
00:16:17,389 --> 00:16:23,347
but in the two tests we conducted
so far, the victor is the Audi.

241
00:16:23,349 --> 00:16:26,307
Yes, it tied with
the McLaren for one of them.

242
00:16:26,309 --> 00:16:31,787
We also did an economy run. And the
Audi won that, as well. Yes, it did.

243
00:16:31,789 --> 00:16:35,267
So, anyway, later on, there will be
more cut-price supercar larks

244
00:16:35,269 --> 00:16:39,907
from Spain. In the meantime,
here is the news.

245
00:16:39,909 --> 00:16:43,707
No, I've got an announcement to
make first. Really?

246
00:16:43,709 --> 00:16:49,227
Yes, last week, in a bid to show
that Britain is not too crowded to

247
00:16:49,229 --> 00:16:55,867
have fun in a nice car, I took
a Ferrari to this road, and I said

248
00:16:55,869 --> 00:16:58,427
that even though this was
just 40 miles from London

249
00:16:58,429 --> 00:17:00,429
in Hertfordshire...

250
00:17:02,269 --> 00:17:03,707
..there was no traffic at all

251
00:17:03,709 --> 00:17:07,147
and you could still enjoy it
in the Ferrari that I was using.

252
00:17:07,149 --> 00:17:12,067
Well, we have been inundated with
complaints, and I do mean inundated.

253
00:17:12,069 --> 00:17:16,147
There have been a lot. A lot.
People were absolutely furious.

254
00:17:16,149 --> 00:17:20,907
"How dare the BBC say this is
Hertfordshire?! It plainly isn't."

255
00:17:20,909 --> 00:17:23,867
Well, you're right,
I admit it, and I apologise.

256
00:17:23,869 --> 00:17:27,269
That is not Hertfordshire.
It's Buckinghamshire, actually.

257
00:17:28,829 --> 00:17:31,187
Nevertheless, well spotted,
all of you, for seeing that.

258
00:17:31,189 --> 00:17:32,667
You were on the ball, there.

259
00:17:32,669 --> 00:17:36,147
Hey, now, we've got some important
consumer news for everybody.

260
00:17:36,149 --> 00:17:39,147
When you go to a car showroom now,
the salesman will try to sell you

261
00:17:39,149 --> 00:17:42,027
lots of electronic bits
and bobs for your car.

262
00:17:42,029 --> 00:17:45,627
Here's our Top Gear top tip -
don't bother with any of them

263
00:17:45,629 --> 00:17:47,627
because they don't work,
any of them.

264
00:17:47,629 --> 00:17:50,467
Bluetooth. Bluetooth never works.
It doesn't.

265
00:17:50,469 --> 00:17:54,147
Hammond uses it and it's like he's
sitting at the bottom of a river.

266
00:17:54,149 --> 00:17:56,587
Well, to be fair, sometimes I am.

267
00:17:56,589 --> 00:18:00,067
Shall I tell you the thing that
doesn't work the most of all?

268
00:18:00,069 --> 00:18:02,547
Voice activation.
That's just a shouting match.

269
00:18:02,549 --> 00:18:05,347
You're driving along, don't have to
take your hands off the wheel.

270
00:18:05,349 --> 00:18:08,027
You go, "Call Richard Hammond."
"Collapsing suspension".

271
00:18:08,029 --> 00:18:10,467
It does!

272
00:18:10,469 --> 00:18:11,747
Oh, it's misunderstood me.

273
00:18:11,749 --> 00:18:14,827
"Call Richard Hammond."

274
00:18:14,829 --> 00:18:16,547
"Deflating tyres."

275
00:18:16,549 --> 00:18:18,787
That's it!

276
00:18:18,789 --> 00:18:20,827
"Reinflate tyres!"

277
00:18:20,829 --> 00:18:23,509
"Reinflate tyres!"
"Calling Richard Hammond."

278
00:18:24,989 --> 00:18:28,867
The problem is that, in the olden
days, when it first came out,

279
00:18:28,869 --> 00:18:31,867
voice activation was just for the
radio or the satellite navigation.

280
00:18:31,869 --> 00:18:34,307
Now it's for every single
feature on the car

281
00:18:34,309 --> 00:18:37,107
and in your life, and it has to
understand every accent

282
00:18:37,109 --> 00:18:38,627
in all of Britain.

283
00:18:38,629 --> 00:18:40,347
"Och aye the noo."

284
00:18:40,349 --> 00:18:41,909
"All right, pet?"

285
00:18:43,349 --> 00:18:46,907
It just can't cope. So, you're
driving along, you go, "Radio Two."

286
00:18:46,909 --> 00:18:49,627
"Accessing bank account."

287
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:51,147
Oh, no!

288
00:18:51,149 --> 00:18:52,867
"Transferring funds."

289
00:18:52,869 --> 00:18:54,907
God, no, don't!

290
00:18:54,909 --> 00:18:58,107
While we're having a moan,
I don't like electric boot closing.

291
00:18:58,109 --> 00:19:02,187
With you on that. What was
the matter with slamming the boot?

292
00:19:02,189 --> 00:19:04,107
So instead of doing that,
it's just...

293
00:19:04,109 --> 00:19:05,627
The idea is that you press the button

294
00:19:05,629 --> 00:19:10,347
and the boot sets off and you can
get in your car, but it's so slow!

295
00:19:10,349 --> 00:19:13,587
By the time you've got in your car,
your dog had seen its opportunity

296
00:19:13,589 --> 00:19:16,267
and made a break for freedom,
he's in the traffic.

297
00:19:16,269 --> 00:19:20,067
Or worse, it detects your
shopping in the boot

298
00:19:20,069 --> 00:19:22,069
and it thinks,
"That could be a child."

299
00:19:23,989 --> 00:19:27,907
Oh, look, it's a packet of dog
biscuits, it's not a baby.

300
00:19:27,909 --> 00:19:30,507
"Firing airbag in three..."

301
00:19:30,509 --> 00:19:32,107
Don't fire the airbag!

302
00:19:32,109 --> 00:19:33,827
Too much responsibility.

303
00:19:33,829 --> 00:19:37,347
Modern cars are deeply irritating
because of the electronics.

304
00:19:37,349 --> 00:19:38,427
Can I move it on now?

305
00:19:38,429 --> 00:19:41,907
Now, last week
I asked if you would send in

306
00:19:41,909 --> 00:19:45,627
photographs of Jeremy
on his new bicycle.

307
00:19:45,629 --> 00:19:49,187
Because... Well, I didn't expect to
get anything because, frankly,

308
00:19:49,189 --> 00:19:52,747
I didn't believe he'd bought
a bike. I have! Well... I have!

309
00:19:52,749 --> 00:19:54,347
Do you know, I now believe you.

310
00:19:54,349 --> 00:19:56,787
I know you have, because somebody
HAS sent in a picture.

311
00:19:56,789 --> 00:19:59,149
And here he is -
Jeremy on his bicycle.

312
00:20:06,709 --> 00:20:09,467
It's, er... It's working.

313
00:20:09,469 --> 00:20:12,067
You are losing weight.
You're trimming down.

314
00:20:12,069 --> 00:20:15,307
That's not my bike.
I haven't got stabilisers.

315
00:20:15,309 --> 00:20:17,827
Otherwise, it's pretty accurate.

316
00:20:17,829 --> 00:20:19,347
I've got some serious news.

317
00:20:19,349 --> 00:20:22,627
A lot of cars these days have got
a sport button on them, OK?

318
00:20:22,629 --> 00:20:26,267
The idea is you push it
and it makes everything more taut
and more racy, OK?

319
00:20:26,269 --> 00:20:30,067
But I've long harboured
a suspicion that it doesn't
actually make the car go any faster.

320
00:20:30,069 --> 00:20:31,147
So last week we did a test.

321
00:20:31,149 --> 00:20:34,187
They've got a new Golf GTI
down here, which incidentally,

322
00:20:34,189 --> 00:20:38,227
is a brilliant, brilliant car.
Extremely good. It's properly good.

323
00:20:38,229 --> 00:20:40,787
Anyway, we got The Stig,
put him in normal mode,

324
00:20:40,789 --> 00:20:44,787
sent him around the track
and he did a 129.6, OK?

325
00:20:44,789 --> 00:20:48,547
We then put it in sport
which beefed up the suspension

326
00:20:48,549 --> 00:20:51,427
and the front differential
and it made the steering heavier

327
00:20:51,429 --> 00:20:55,547
and it quickened the throttle, OK?
In sport, 129.6.

328
00:20:55,549 --> 00:20:58,027
What, exactly the same?
Exactly the same.

329
00:20:58,029 --> 00:21:01,427
We then put it in comfort mode,
makes everything soft and gooey.

330
00:21:01,429 --> 00:21:04,867
129.5. Fast!

331
00:21:04,869 --> 00:21:05,987
Faster.

332
00:21:05,989 --> 00:21:10,227
That is confirmation
that the sport button just makes
a car more uncomfortable.

333
00:21:10,229 --> 00:21:11,707
Yeah, it shouldn't say "sport",

334
00:21:11,709 --> 00:21:13,427
it should just say, "worse".

335
00:21:13,429 --> 00:21:15,107
Now, there's a new supercar.

336
00:21:15,109 --> 00:21:19,667
It is called the... Icona Vulcano.
Here it is.

337
00:21:19,669 --> 00:21:23,947
Jeremy, did you do
that publicity photograph?

338
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:25,667
That's what
I call a publicity shot.

339
00:21:25,669 --> 00:21:28,947
I love that very much.
Not sure about the car, though.

340
00:21:28,949 --> 00:21:33,107
They say it has a V12 hybrid,
but they won't tell us

341
00:21:33,109 --> 00:21:36,267
where the V12's from or
how the hybrid system works.

342
00:21:36,269 --> 00:21:39,907
All they will say
is it develops 950 horsepower

343
00:21:39,909 --> 00:21:42,067
and will go 217 miles an hour.

344
00:21:42,069 --> 00:21:44,387
Does it? Mmm, mmm.

345
00:21:44,389 --> 00:21:48,707
The reason I brought this car up
is their chief design director,

346
00:21:48,709 --> 00:21:52,467
his name is Samuel Chuffart.

347
00:21:52,469 --> 00:21:55,107
Give over.

348
00:21:55,109 --> 00:21:56,867
It's not.

349
00:21:56,869 --> 00:22:02,067
His name is not Chuffart.
It's not! Chuffart. Lovely.

350
00:22:02,069 --> 00:22:05,229
There's a man with fond
memories of his school days!

351
00:22:06,549 --> 00:22:10,427
Every register, "Oh, no, it's got to
Christian, I'm next." "Chuffart".

352
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:13,347
"A-ha-ha-ha." I bet the
novelty never wore off for him.

353
00:22:13,349 --> 00:22:15,867
Apparently,
he worked at Jaguar for a while.

354
00:22:15,869 --> 00:22:18,549
I'm not sure what happened there.
They probably had to let him go.

355
00:22:21,709 --> 00:22:24,267
So now he's ended up in Italy,
because that is an Italian firm.

356
00:22:24,269 --> 00:22:26,067
They're actually making
the car in China.

357
00:22:26,069 --> 00:22:29,067
Can you imagine what
the wiring's going to be like?

358
00:22:29,069 --> 00:22:33,067
Chuffart in Italian probably means
"hat penis" anyway, or something.

359
00:22:33,069 --> 00:22:36,067
We actually asked our researchers
to call up this company and say,

360
00:22:36,069 --> 00:22:38,347
"Can you tell us more about
the car?" And not one of them

361
00:22:38,349 --> 00:22:41,227
could get through the beginning bit
of the call without bursting...

362
00:22:41,229 --> 00:22:43,707
The receptionist on the other end
must be used to the phone

363
00:22:43,709 --> 00:22:46,787
ringing and there's
someone laughing,
"Yeah, I'll put you through."

364
00:22:46,789 --> 00:22:48,147
"Hello, Chuffart."

365
00:22:48,149 --> 00:22:54,789
He probably just answers the phone
with the words, "Yes, that is
my name. Let's clear the air now."

366
00:22:56,069 --> 00:22:58,347
That's how that picture came about.

367
00:22:58,349 --> 00:23:01,189
Someone lit a match just after
Chuff farted!

368
00:23:03,829 --> 00:23:07,827
Moving on. Because this week we are
testing the McLaren 12C Spider,

369
00:23:07,829 --> 00:23:11,987
the Ferrari 458 Spider
and the Audi R8 V10.

370
00:23:11,989 --> 00:23:15,987
Let me guess, is it Spider?
Do you know, it is. It is a Spider.

371
00:23:15,989 --> 00:23:19,427
We have chosen budget supercars
because we are in Spain,

372
00:23:19,429 --> 00:23:21,867
where the economic problems
are terrible.

373
00:23:21,869 --> 00:23:24,067
Yeah,
so far we've been to a ghost town.

374
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:26,347
It had a hospital,
it had a school, had restaurants,

375
00:23:26,349 --> 00:23:29,427
had thousands of houses and flats,
but no people at all.

376
00:23:29,429 --> 00:23:32,347
We've been on a road that
went nowhere.

377
00:23:32,349 --> 00:23:34,427
It was like filming in
a ghost country, actually.

378
00:23:34,429 --> 00:23:38,549
Anyway, we pick up the story
after a night in a hotel in Granada.

379
00:24:01,549 --> 00:24:03,467
We headed north
the following morning,

380
00:24:03,469 --> 00:24:07,429
worried that we'd hit the rush-hour
traffic. However...

381
00:24:10,389 --> 00:24:14,787
So there's only three cars on this
motorway and we're in all of them.

382
00:24:14,789 --> 00:24:17,987
Look at that.
Our own personal motorway.

383
00:24:17,989 --> 00:24:19,989
I've always wanted a motorway.

384
00:24:21,149 --> 00:24:22,627
Since no-one was around,

385
00:24:22,629 --> 00:24:25,069
we thought we would see
how fast our cars would go.

386
00:24:26,949 --> 00:24:28,829
We just need to find a straight bit.

387
00:24:30,869 --> 00:24:32,429
Now, this is quite straight.

388
00:24:34,829 --> 00:24:39,347
At 200 miles an hour, this slight
corner becomes a hairpin bend.

389
00:24:39,349 --> 00:24:40,469
We need arrow straight.

390
00:24:42,509 --> 00:24:47,149
'When we did eventually find a long
enough straight, it had goats on it.

391
00:24:48,429 --> 00:24:53,269
'So we were about to give up
on our top speed run, but then...'

392
00:24:54,349 --> 00:24:55,349
Ooh, an airport.

393
00:24:56,989 --> 00:25:01,547
Chaps, is that an airport? I just
thought... Yes, aeropuerto, it is.

394
00:25:01,549 --> 00:25:03,907
Well, if the runway's as busy
as the roads,

395
00:25:03,909 --> 00:25:06,989
we might be able to
use the runway for our speed test.

396
00:25:13,189 --> 00:25:16,427
God, there's some parking available!

397
00:25:16,429 --> 00:25:18,509
All of it in fact.

398
00:25:21,789 --> 00:25:24,069
Er... Where is everyone?

399
00:25:29,069 --> 00:25:33,349
'We went inside to
look for someone in charge.'

400
00:25:34,509 --> 00:25:36,189
Hello?

401
00:25:38,229 --> 00:25:39,309
Hello?

402
00:25:40,269 --> 00:25:43,189
'But the whole place
was completely deserted.'

403
00:25:46,429 --> 00:25:50,067
The computers are all on, look!
I can make a baggage check.

404
00:25:50,069 --> 00:25:53,509
I can log on!
I've got one of those things that
goes... I can check you in!

405
00:25:57,709 --> 00:25:58,707
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

406
00:25:58,709 --> 00:26:01,987
The wheel's coming off.
My wheel's come off!

407
00:26:01,989 --> 00:26:04,707
Hello. I'll be Lufthansa.
I am sorry, the gate is closed.

408
00:26:04,709 --> 00:26:08,147
Well, can you just open it? Nein.

409
00:26:08,149 --> 00:26:11,949
I haven't got a passport,
I've just got a selection of weapons
and some concealed drugs.

410
00:26:15,069 --> 00:26:17,829
Eventually, though,
we found what we came for.

411
00:26:18,989 --> 00:26:21,189
That is a runway over there,
I believe. Yes.

412
00:26:23,909 --> 00:26:27,667
'But since there was no-one around
to ask for permission to use it,

413
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:29,987
'we had to improvise.'

414
00:26:29,989 --> 00:26:33,267
Would it be possible for us
to drive on the runway here?

415
00:26:33,269 --> 00:26:37,347
Is there any flight traffic today?
No, it's very quiet today.

416
00:26:37,349 --> 00:26:39,229
I imagine it'll be fine.

417
00:26:44,509 --> 00:26:47,669
With permission granted,
we headed out to the runway.

418
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:52,029
It's all right, I've got it.
I've got it. It's OK.

419
00:26:53,229 --> 00:26:55,389
I can't do manual labour,
you know that.

420
00:26:59,709 --> 00:27:00,709
Look at that!

421
00:27:02,669 --> 00:27:03,669
It's ours!

422
00:27:14,869 --> 00:27:19,067
The runway was
a whopping 2.5 miles long.

423
00:27:19,069 --> 00:27:21,469
More than enough to max our cars.

424
00:27:24,109 --> 00:27:26,427
Hammond elected to go first.

425
00:27:26,429 --> 00:27:29,427
I'm always nervous
when he drives in a straight line.

426
00:27:29,429 --> 00:27:32,267
"Richard Hammond, can you drive
in a straight line down a runway?

427
00:27:32,269 --> 00:27:34,189
"Yes, what can possibly go
wrong with that?"

428
00:27:35,349 --> 00:27:38,987
Hit the launch control button
with it, in race and manual.

429
00:27:38,989 --> 00:27:42,067
Give it max revs, my right foot.
ENGINE REVS

430
00:27:42,069 --> 00:27:43,949
Left foot off.
Right, we're away!

431
00:27:45,149 --> 00:27:47,827
It does the first gear
change for me, now it's up to me,

432
00:27:47,829 --> 00:27:49,947
and already we're doing 85, 90...

433
00:27:49,949 --> 00:27:54,227
100 miles an hour, that quickly.

434
00:27:54,229 --> 00:27:55,589
Damn, this thing is fast!

435
00:27:58,989 --> 00:28:01,427
Oh, look at the dust cloud.

436
00:28:01,429 --> 00:28:04,627
138, 141.

437
00:28:04,629 --> 00:28:08,187
I can hear the grit
hitting the underside of the car.
There's a lot of it.

438
00:28:08,189 --> 00:28:12,707
Seventh gear has just been hit.
175 miles an hour.

439
00:28:12,709 --> 00:28:13,787
Still accelerating hard.

440
00:28:13,789 --> 00:28:18,427
I can see the line, 186...87, 88.

441
00:28:18,429 --> 00:28:20,227
Come on, Ferrari, accelerate!

442
00:28:20,229 --> 00:28:25,229
Now that is a Ferrari at full chat.
90. 91.

443
00:28:26,509 --> 00:28:27,509
92.

444
00:28:28,549 --> 00:28:31,347
92, 93.

445
00:28:31,349 --> 00:28:34,469
193 miles an hour.
Top speed achieved.

446
00:28:36,429 --> 00:28:38,107
Next up, it was James,

447
00:28:38,109 --> 00:28:42,587
who decided to use absolutely
all of the available space.

448
00:28:42,589 --> 00:28:47,067
Right, here we go. Sport,
sport suspension, air con is off.

449
00:28:47,069 --> 00:28:50,069
Manual one. Here we go at the max.

450
00:28:53,869 --> 00:28:56,867
Right, here he comes now.
Captain Slow is his name.

451
00:28:56,869 --> 00:28:58,629
Or the Italians call him
"Mr Slowly".

452
00:29:01,749 --> 00:29:03,747
That's 80.

453
00:29:03,749 --> 00:29:06,347
I know at some point in that car,
when he's doing his run,

454
00:29:06,349 --> 00:29:08,147
he is saying, "buffeting".

455
00:29:08,149 --> 00:29:09,949
Buffeting.

456
00:29:11,629 --> 00:29:15,067
He's moving along
in the right direction.

457
00:29:15,069 --> 00:29:17,947
It's weird to think James May
in that, doing that speed.

458
00:29:17,949 --> 00:29:19,589
A spaniel in control of that.

459
00:29:21,349 --> 00:29:24,309
Indicated 175, 177. Come on!

460
00:29:28,069 --> 00:29:30,989
That said 186.

461
00:29:32,149 --> 00:29:35,347
Knowing that modern-day
speedos are frighteningly accurate,

462
00:29:35,349 --> 00:29:40,467
I knew what speed I had to beat -
Hammond's, 193.

463
00:29:40,469 --> 00:29:47,029
OK, launch control. First gear.
Press launch. Launch active.

464
00:29:48,589 --> 00:29:50,907
Three, two, one. Go!

465
00:29:50,909 --> 00:29:53,389
Oh, wow, that's quick!

466
00:29:55,549 --> 00:29:57,669
80 miles an hour already.

467
00:29:59,109 --> 00:30:02,389
Here he comes.
He's moving at tremendous speed.

468
00:30:05,189 --> 00:30:09,187
140. I'm taking manual control now

469
00:30:09,189 --> 00:30:10,467
to lock in in six.

470
00:30:10,469 --> 00:30:13,267
I don't want to go into seventh

471
00:30:13,269 --> 00:30:16,427
