taught that. What, how to punch?

702
00:43:11,429 --> 00:43:13,907
Yeah. Hollywood fu, it was great
fun.

703
00:43:13,909 --> 00:43:17,867
Do you punch like... Do you punch
with that side of your hand?

704
00:43:17,869 --> 00:43:19,507
What are you doing? When you punch.

705
00:43:19,509 --> 00:43:22,427
You look like you're trying to wipe
a windscreen or something.

706
00:43:22,429 --> 00:43:25,227
No, when you punch somebody,
cos I've often... You sometimes...

707
00:43:25,229 --> 00:43:27,947
Normally, you're quite tight and
it's all from the waist,

708
00:43:27,949 --> 00:43:31,347
but you have to sell it a bit more
for the camera, so you arc it round
a bit.

709
00:43:31,349 --> 00:43:34,947
You could try it. Shall we try it
now? Shall we try a fake punch?

710
00:43:34,949 --> 00:43:36,507
Yeah!

711
00:43:36,509 --> 00:43:38,427
What if it turns into a real one?

712
00:43:38,429 --> 00:43:40,869
I'll give and you receive.

713
00:43:43,429 --> 00:43:45,027
I like being the dominant one.

714
00:43:45,029 --> 00:43:46,947
So, there's the camera. That one?

715
00:43:46,949 --> 00:43:50,067
Facing me. You're actually directing
now! Yeah! Facing you...

716
00:43:50,069 --> 00:43:51,827
Am I ready for this punch? Yeah.

717
00:43:51,829 --> 00:43:55,189
When I get to about there, you can
move your head. But what if I don't?

718
00:43:56,909 --> 00:43:58,307
I'm not going to do that.

719
00:43:58,309 --> 00:44:01,509
Is anybody... Your dry-cleaning
bills when my nose...!

720
00:44:02,549 --> 00:44:04,067
All right. Are you ready? Yes.

721
00:44:04,069 --> 00:44:05,949
OK, and...

722
00:44:08,709 --> 00:44:10,509
Did that look all right?
He knows, they know.

723
00:44:14,949 --> 00:44:17,867
We've had many actors on the show
over the years, sitting there,

724
00:44:17,869 --> 00:44:20,387
but we've never had one who's been
carjacked before.

725
00:44:20,389 --> 00:44:22,587
Oh, really? That's good.

726
00:44:22,589 --> 00:44:24,947
It is, but you were genuinely
carjacked.

727
00:44:24,949 --> 00:44:26,947
I was genuinely carjacked. Yeah.

728
00:44:26,949 --> 00:44:28,467
Scary? How did it happen?

729
00:44:28,469 --> 00:44:29,867
It was very scary.

730
00:44:29,869 --> 00:44:32,987
I have to emphasise,
not just because I love South Africa

731
00:44:32,989 --> 00:44:34,187
and South Africans,

732
00:44:34,189 --> 00:44:37,827
but it was a small event in a very
big country, and we were very lucky.

733
00:44:37,829 --> 00:44:40,787
We were on a bumpy dirt track
and had gone onto the N2,

734
00:44:40,789 --> 00:44:43,627
the major trunk
road down the east coast,

735
00:44:43,629 --> 00:44:47,547
and the front right tyre blew
and these guys surrounded us,

736
00:44:47,549 --> 00:44:51,307
stuff went on with belongings
and we were pushed about a bit.

737
00:44:51,309 --> 00:44:53,667
I was put in the boot of the car,
though, at one point,

738
00:44:53,669 --> 00:44:55,467
and that was interesting.

739
00:44:55,469 --> 00:44:58,467
I thought, "Maybe I could diffuse
the brake lights,

740
00:44:58,469 --> 00:44:59,547
"then the police..."

741
00:44:59,549 --> 00:45:02,747
No, no policeman in South Africa
is going to pull over a car

742
00:45:02,749 --> 00:45:05,987
full of men at midnight to
question a broken taillight.

743
00:45:05,989 --> 00:45:08,627
But it was very scary.

744
00:45:08,629 --> 00:45:12,187
When they got you out again, did
they not put a duvet over your head?

745
00:45:12,189 --> 00:45:14,747
At one point,
stuff was being thrown out the car.

746
00:45:14,749 --> 00:45:16,907
We were underneath this underpass

747
00:45:16,909 --> 00:45:19,787
and these juggernauts were just
charging over

748
00:45:19,789 --> 00:45:22,227
and the sound cover
would be perfect for a quiet pop.

749
00:45:22,229 --> 00:45:25,587
Then this duvet got thrown out, just
went over our head, and I thought,

750
00:45:25,589 --> 00:45:27,267
"Again, it's the pillow thing,

751
00:45:27,269 --> 00:45:29,747
"it's going to be a muffler for
a gunshot."

752
00:45:29,749 --> 00:45:31,947
So I kind of came to terms
with mortality

753
00:45:31,949 --> 00:45:35,467
and dying on my own about four
times in the space of half an hour.

754
00:45:35,469 --> 00:45:37,467
The whole thing
went on for about two hours.

755
00:45:37,469 --> 00:45:40,147
We mustn't put people off southern
Africa. No, we mustn't.

756
00:45:40,149 --> 00:45:41,707
It's a big, beautiful place. It is.

757
00:45:41,709 --> 00:45:44,669
So we could just ignore all that, it
doesn't really happen! Cut that!

758
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:49,149
Anyway, so, you came down here to
do your lap. Oh, BLEEP!

759
00:45:50,949 --> 00:45:53,067
And how was it out there?
It was really good fun.

760
00:45:53,069 --> 00:45:55,947
The first couple of laps, I couldn't
see the wood for the trees,

761
00:45:55,949 --> 00:45:57,547
but as it went on, I think I got...

762
00:45:57,549 --> 00:45:58,867
I bettered my times later on,

763
00:45:58,869 --> 00:46:01,347
so I was obviously learning
something. How do you know?

764
00:46:01,349 --> 00:46:03,027
People would go, "Mmm."

765
00:46:03,029 --> 00:46:05,027
Oh, just from people's "Mmm"?

766
00:46:05,029 --> 00:46:08,187
I'm told you did more laps than
any guest we've had.

767
00:46:08,189 --> 00:46:10,227
Oh, that's so shaming!

768
00:46:10,229 --> 00:46:12,747
Who'd like to see the fastest lap?

769
00:46:12,749 --> 00:46:13,749
Yeah!

770
00:46:14,789 --> 00:46:16,667
Let's have a look.

771
00:46:16,669 --> 00:46:17,907
OK.

772
00:46:17,909 --> 00:46:18,949
Oh, yes.

773
00:46:21,069 --> 00:46:22,069
We are away.

774
00:46:23,509 --> 00:46:25,309
Yippee ki-yay, mother-BLEEP!

775
00:46:26,869 --> 00:46:28,469
A fan of The Hangover is here!

776
00:46:29,549 --> 00:46:33,189
Look at it grip,
with a lifetime warranty.

777
00:46:35,629 --> 00:46:37,869
That's not bad.
Is that all right? Yeah.

778
00:46:38,869 --> 00:46:39,909
It is hot in here.

779
00:46:40,949 --> 00:46:42,547
That's no excuse, come on.

780
00:46:42,549 --> 00:46:46,147
Did you have the air conditioning
off or on? Off. Good man.

781
00:46:46,149 --> 00:46:49,347
A bit wide through there,
maybe costing you half a second.

782
00:46:49,349 --> 00:46:53,469
Gear change, gear change, gear
change, gear change. So... boom.

783
00:46:55,429 --> 00:46:58,869
Yeah, like the Sundance Kid there,
very quick mover! Oh, God!

784
00:47:00,709 --> 00:47:02,827
Bit slow, but at least you're not
skidding about.

785
00:47:02,829 --> 00:47:06,187
You haven't really used all
the track - or, indeed, any of it.
Anyway...

786
00:47:06,189 --> 00:47:09,069
Use the track, Benedict.

787
00:47:11,149 --> 00:47:15,747
Ladies and gentlemen, Alec Guinness
in the Reasonably Priced Car!

788
00:47:15,749 --> 00:47:17,507
Moved those, that was well done.

789
00:47:17,509 --> 00:47:19,987
And now here it is,
second-to-last corner.

790
00:47:19,989 --> 00:47:21,547
Holy crap, this is scary.

791
00:47:21,549 --> 00:47:24,387
No, that is
pretty much perfect. Is it?

792
00:47:24,389 --> 00:47:26,747
That really is perfect, Gambon.

793
00:47:26,749 --> 00:47:29,949
Ooh, fast. Ooh, fast,
but not Jimmy Carr. Across the line!

794
00:47:35,189 --> 00:47:38,109
Ah, not bad! That is all right.
That is all right.

795
00:47:41,269 --> 00:47:44,827
These are the times we have so far
in our Reasonably Priced Car.

796
00:47:44,829 --> 00:47:45,787
Ooh, crikey.

797
00:47:45,789 --> 00:47:47,427
Where do we think?

798
00:47:47,429 --> 00:47:48,987
I don't know, I don't know.

799
00:47:48,989 --> 00:47:51,467
Maybe faster than Warwick, I'd be
happy with that.

